name: Sidemen Bali Swing
address: Telaga Tawang, Sidemen, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80864, Indonesia
review 1: Really nice local Bali swing. 200.000 per person. Friendly people, we made gorgeous photos.
review 2: Lovely views, actually more fun than I expected. The man worked hard for his money! We paid 150k pp.
review 3: Amazing and relaxing view of Sidemen Valley while swinging
review 4:
Amazing swing in Sidemen, beautiful location and very friendly owner!
Reasonably priced and makes great photos!

name: Kubu Taru
address: Jl. Semarapura-Karangasem, Telaga Tawang, Kec. Sidemen, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80642, Indonesia
review 1:
We really enjoyed our stay in Kubu Taru. The location is great and out of turisty, busy areas. The views are nice on green fields and mt Agung.
The owner is really nice too and also the lady which was cooking and looking after rooms.
The food there is really good.
The beautifull wooden huts just add on great atmosphere.
It is next to the road but we didn't find it too loud.
review 2: Loved my stay at Kubu Taru... the manager Gusti was so friendly and welcoming (all the staff was). The views are amazing, the food delicious:) I really enjoyed the bungalow setting.
review 3: View is beautiful, but sadly it's too close to the main road so not very peaceful. And a little far from all the restaurants. Unfortunately I changed my hotel, stayed only 1 night.
review 4: We ate here and the food was fantastic, a really lovely dinner and lunch spot!! The curry was outstanding!
review 5: Kubu Taru is a hidden gem. It brings beautiful rice fields right to your doorstep. It has a very raw and organic vibe. Beautiful way to watch the world pass you by as you are surrounded by greenery and mountains

name: Warung Telaga
address: Desa, Telaga Tawang, Kec. Sidemen, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80864, Indonesia
review 1:
Stopped here for lunch after visiting Gembleng Waterfall.
Nice setting, beautiful clean kitchen, good food and plenty of parking.
review 2: Good warung to make a pit stop with views in this scenic road to Sideman valley. Ayam goreng and tempe are delicious (just ask what is fresh or available). We also got the hot tea with ginger, also nice. Lady running the shop is very friendly. Note for Bules prices are somewhat fluid :), just ask in advance.
review 3:
Pros: very tasty food, nice view, got food relatively fast
Cons: don’t trust the pictures on the menu: we received 4 spring rolls instead of the depicted 6 and also didn’t receive a side salad (even though we specifically asked whether it was included before ordering). They then just said “not available”. Prices are relatively high, too, compared to other warungs
review 4: Tasty food, kind service and beautiful view at the mountains and rice terraces.
review 5:
Our host stayed up late in the night for us after our boat had arrived much later than expected. After our taxi dropped us off at the wrong place he even picked us up, offered us drinks and he remained very friendly and open even though he had to get up early.
The area here is beautiful and calming, breakfast was delicious and the guest houses are very cozy.

name: Sidemen sunset point and mini bar
address: Telaga Tawang, Sidemen, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80864, Indonesia
review 1: Amazing swing in Sidemen away from the touristy place, beautiful location and very friendly owner! Reasonably priced and makes great photos! Highly recommend this place if you visit sidemen.
review 2: Very friendly operators, beautiful site and safety is their #1 priority!!!
review 3: Amazing place and really friendly local people !!!!

name: Satay fish and convenience store
address: GC7R+QX6, Jl. Semarapura-Karangasem, Telaga Tawang, Kec. Sidemen, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80864, Indonesia
review 1: The satay fish, pepes ikan, lemongrass sambal and chilli sambal are to die for. This little place uses unique family recipes for these dishes, you have to try them. Come around 10am to get it fresh. The family is very friendly and honest (helpful to use translate app if you want to chat). In February 2023 one person can have a meal of these delicacies plus rice for around $2 (Australian) depending on how much you guzzle. It is located across the road from Pura Dadia Pasek Gelgel di Bloncing (not inside it).
